7}, {"name": "cardiovascular disease", "mentions": 2, "confidence_score": 17, "total_score": 34}], "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Stipagrostis zittelii are fever, which is often treated with a decoction of the plant's roots, reducing body temperature and alleviating symptoms. This plant has also been traditionally used to treat rheumatism, providing relief from joint pain and inflammation due to its anti-inflammatory properties. In some regions, Stipagrostis zittelii is employed to cure diarrhea, its extracts having been shown to exhibit antimicrobial activity against certain pathogens that cause gastrointestinal infections. Furthermore, the plant's leaves and stems are used to treat coughs, their expectorant properties helping to loosen and clear mucus from the respiratory tract. Additionally, Stipagrostis zittelii has been used to heal wounds, accelerating the healing process through its antibacterial and antifungal properties.", "properties": [{"name": "antimicrobial", "mentions": 19, "confidence_score": 131, "total_score": 2489}, {"name": "antioxidant", "mentions": 19, "confidence_score": 125, "total_score": 2375}, {"name": "anti-inflammatory", "mentions": 19, "confidence_score": 122, "total_score": 2318}, {"name": "antidiabetic", "mentions": 10, "confidence_score": 41, "total_score": 410}, {"name": "cardioprotective", "mentions": 9, "confidence_score": 40, "total_score": 360}, {"name": "antifungal", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 38, "total_score": 304}, {"name": "antibacterial", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 28, "total_score": 140}, {"name": "analgesic", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 28, "total_score": 224}, {"name": "anticancer", "mentions": 12, "confidence_score": 28, "total_score": 336}, {"name": "wound-healing", "mentions": 4, "confidence_score": 27, "total_score": 108}, {"name": "hepatoprotective", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 24, "total_score": 120}, {"name": "antihypertensive", "mentions": 7, "con